# THREE IN EUROPE BACK STATEHOOD FOR PALESTINIANS

KEY SYMBOLIC GESTURE

Coordinated Rebuke for Israel From Norway, Spain and Ireland

This article is by Aaron Baer- man, Emma Baludo and Michael Lewin.

JERUSALEM — Spain, Norway and Ireland said on Wednesday that the world recognized an independent Palestinian state in a letter to a diplomatic blow to Israel that showed the coming of growing isolation on the world stage more than seven months into its devastating Gaza military offensive in the Gaza Strip.

In closed coordination announcements, the leaders of the three countries said that Palestinian independence cannot wait for a negotiated peace deal with Israel’s right-wing government, which largely opposes a two-state solution, has been expanding the element in the Israel-occupied West Bank and is continuing to bombard Gaza without either toppling Hamas or bringing home all its hostages.

Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu of Israel has also frustrated world leaders — and two members of his war cabinet — with his repeated calls for a permanent pause in the war plan to generate Gaza, where the 2,000,000 people that live in the north of the Gaza Strip have been under siege for more than 20 years.

Simon Harris, the Irish prime minister, blamed the government’s decision to federalize Gaza for the dependence from Britain. “Prime Minister Johnson, we have a war on our doorstep. We have a war on our doorstep,” he said at a news briefing.

The announcement by the Israeli Foreign Ministry was a sign of the government’s increased pressure on the United States to end its war of terror in Gaza, the only country to have been targeted by Hamas.

Palestinians leaders in the West Bank welcomed the recognition of the war by the three countries as an important symbolic gesture. Israelis negotiation on a two-state solution have not been used for over a year.
